article.headline: TCU 78, Wyoming 60
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Ronnie Moss finished with 27 points and 10 rebounds to lead TCU to a 78-60 victory over Wyoming on Wednesday night. Garlon Green added 16 points to help the Horned Frogs (10-8, 1-2 Mountain West) end a four-game losing streak. Francisco Cruz led the Cowboys (8-9, 1-2) with 16 points, and Amath M'Baye had 13. TCU never trailed and took a double-digit lead for good on Moss's 3-pointer with 5:10 left in the first half. Moss finished with six 3s and had four steals. Amric Fields, Nikola Cerina and Greg Hill each added 10 points for the Horned Frogs. TCU led 39-23 at halftime and pushed its advantage to 26 in the second half.
